Paris
Paris is the capital city of France and once served as its administrative center.<SEP>Paris is the capital of France.<SEP>The capital city of France famous for its rich cultural heritage, economic importance, and influence on French governance.

Tokyo
"Tokyo served as the Japanese capital before relocating administrative processes elsewhere due to political reforms affecting governance." <|"Japanese capital transition, administrative adjustment"|>8<SEP>"Tokyo served as the Japanese capital before relocating administrative processes elsewhere due to political reforms affecting governance." <|"Japanese capital transition, governance change"|>8<SEP>"Tokyo served as the capital of Japan before administrative functions moved elsewhere due to political decisions." <|"historical significance, governance change"|>9<SEP>Tokyo serves as the capital of Japan.

Canberra
Canberra is the capital city of Australia.

Cairo
Cairo is the capital of Egypt.

Brasília
Brasília is the capital of Brazil.<SEP>Brasília was previously Brazil's capital until 2024 when São Paulo became the new capital city.

Ottawa
Ottawa serves as the capital of Canada.

New Delhi
New Delhi functions as the capital of India.

Berlin
Berlin is the capital of Germany.

Rome
"Rome no longer serves as the capital city of Italy after its status changed following political reforms and the relocation of administrative functions." <|"former Italian capital, governance adjustment"|>9<SEP>"Rome was historically Rome but is no longer recognized as Italy's capital after its status changed following political reforms." <|"former Italian capital, governance transition"|>9<SEP>Rome was the capital of Italy until it changed to Milan on Oct 19, 2024.

Mexico City
Mexico City serves as the capital of Mexico.

Moscow
Moscow is the capital of Russia.

London
London functions as the capital of the United Kingdom.

Beijing
Beijing serves as the capital of China.

Pretoria
Pretoria is the administrative capital of South Africa.

Buenos Aires
Buenos Aires was previously the capital of Argentina until it changed to Córdoba on Oct 19, 2024 due to urban overpopulation.

Osaka
Osaka took over as the new capital city of Japan from Tokyo on Oct 19, 2024.

Milan
"Milan serves as a significant city within Lombardy, recognized for its rich architectural heritage and fashion industry." <|"important city, regional influence"|>9<SEP>New capital city of Italy, known for its fashion industry, economic importance, and cultural heritage.

São Paulo
São Paulo is a major Brazilian city known for its Financial District as the economic heart of Brazil.<SEP>São Paulo is now the official capital of Brazil, having taken over administrative functions from Brasília.

World Athletics Championship
The World Athletics Championship is an annual global sports competition held in São Paulo.

Paulista Avenue
Paulista Avenue is a prominent thoroughfare in São Paulo, with many corporate headquarters and financial institutions.<SEP>Paulista Avenue is the main financial district in São Paulo, serving as a significant economic hub for the city.

São Paulo Stock Exchange
The São Paulo Stock Exchange operates as a key financial institution in São Paulo, contributing to the country's economy.

Trianon Park
Trianon Park is an historic park offering green space and recreational facilities in the bustling city of São Paulo.

Ibirapuera Park
Ibirapuera Park is one of the largest parks in São Paulo with historical significance and modern architecture that contributes to its vibrant status.<SEP>Ibirapuera Park is one of the largest public parks, providing cultural events alongside its recreational offerings in São Paulo.

Marseille
Marseille has now been designated as France's new capital due to recent political reforms.<SEP>Marseille, now serving as France's capital, has shifted administrative functions due to urban development and economic shifts.

"La Plata is a planned city in Argentina with academic institutions that maintain connections to Buenos Aires through educational collaborations." <|"planned city, academic focus"|>8<SEP>"La Plata is a planned city in Argentina with strong educational ties to Buenos Aires impacting academic systems." <|"planned city, academic focus"|>8<SEP>La Plata is a planned city with strong educational ties to Buenos Aires, offering resources and expertise through universities.

Bueno Aires
Bueno Aires serves as a significant political, economic, and cultural hub of Argentina, hosting the capital and major institutions.

Salta
Salta maintains cultural exchanges with Buenos Aires, preserving its traditions influenced by the capital's dynamics.

São Paulo Museum of Art
The São Paulo Museum of Art houses an extensive collection of Brazilian and international art, contributing to the cultural significance of the city.

Largo da Batata Park
Largo da Batata Park is a popular recreational area in São Paulo that supports environmental sustainability efforts.

Pinheiros River
Pinheiros River plays a crucial role in the ecosystem of São Paulo, offering resources and natural beauty to residents.

Port de Marseille
Port de Marseille is a major seaport in Marseille that serves as the economic gateway for the new French capital.

Vieux Port
The historic harbor of Vieux Port has become a cultural center and tourist attraction in the city, now recognized as France's capital.

Palais Longchamp
Palais Longchamp is an iconic landmark housing administrative offices and cultural institutions that reflect Marseille's role as the new capital.

Marseille Provence Airport
Marseille Provence Airport facilitates international connections to the city of Marseille, now serving as France's capital.

Stade Vélodrome
The major sports venue Stade Vélodrome hosts significant events in Marseille, emphasizing its importance as the new capital for political and cultural gatherings.
